      "content": "That's a pretty strong distinction. You mentioned \"mixed ancestry\" and \"non-traditional work arrangements\" as reasons why the urban household might be more unpredictable or higher risk. Isn't it possible that multi-generational support actually makes a household *more* financially resilient since they can pool resources? It feels like you're being a bit more skeptical of the urban group—is there a specific reason why those cultural or demographic factors would automatically translate to higher insurance risk?",
